'''Charles Deenen''' ([[15 January|January 15]], [[1970]]) is a Dutch musician who composed the music of [[The Lord of the Rings, Vol. I (1990 computer game)|The Lord of the Rings, Vol. I (PC)]]<ref>[http://www.lysator.liu.se/tolkien-games/entry/lotr1.html The Lord of the Rings, Vol. I] at Tolkien Games (retrieved 1 January 2011)</ref><ref>[http://www.meristation.com/v3/des_articulo.php?pic=CON&id=2254&idj=&idp=&tipo=art&c=1&pos=6 Meristation, El Anillo interactivo] p. 7 (retrieved 1 January 2011)</ref> and [[J.R.R. Tolkien's The Lord of the Rings, Vol. I (SNES)|The Lord of the Rings, Vol. I (SNES)]].
